This app is so close to replacing the only IOS app truly missing on Android i.e Garageband.  I feel a bit of loving attention to the interface and workflow and this will be a killer app.  Little things like resizing the tracks or even the keyboard (despite it having a slider to do this) did not leap out at me.  However, in some ways it¬¥s better than Garageband.  Changing octaves for example is very intuitive.  However, I am yet to find a way to turn the metronome off.  I think the guitar requiring two hands to play is a mistake. Although plainly more realistic, it¬¥s not practical on a mobile device or in fact, anything except a guitar.  Garageband handles this well.  The piano keyboard is fine though IOS managed touch sensitivity (I¬¥m guessing by using the size of the finger impression on the screen) which is missing on this app.  I don¬¥t expect this app to have all the funky accompaniment grooves that Garageband has but you can see an attempt has been made in this direction which is impressive.  I really hope the developer invests some time in the really dull stuff, the tiny details to take this to a really smooth, glossy product because here we nearly have a gem.

content: I installed this app, used it to record for 5 seconds and now my microphone on my nexus 7 no longer works. At all. Thanks guys for breaking my tablet! You owe me a new one.  *REPLY*  With my device on a table, unmoving, I created a track and hit record, I wanted to seesee where the recording level was at. Recorded for 5 second, then hit stop. It recorded audio, at quite a high level. I deleted that audio track, created a new track and suddenly the program crashed. When I reopened it, created a new track, no mic level. Closed, tried again. Reboot, try again. Use Google now, no mic. Skype, no mic. The device hadn't been moved, only the software had used the mic and it WAS working when the program crashed as I had just finished recording with it. I don't know what else it could have been.
replyContent:
It is impossible that the application can break the microphone.We did a lot of testing on devices widely used as Nexus7.
RecordingStudio have been installed 1331 times on Nexus 7, no one has reported problems with the microphone.The app is installed on more than 27,000 devices.The app uses  the standard methods provided by Android to capture audio.
